          "credit": "US DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE",
          "content": "### SURVEILLANCE LOG: MISSION 3101\n**DATE:** October 16, 1962\n**SECTOR:** San Cristobal, Cuba\n\n**The Smoking Gun:**\nThe images on the light table are grainy, black-and-white photos taken from 70,000 feet by Major Richard Heyser’s U-2 spy plane. To the untrained eye, they look like smudges in the jungle. But to the CIA photo-interpreters at the National Photographic Interpretation Center (NPIC), the shapes are unmistakable.\n\n**Visual Confirmation:**\nAnalysts have identified canvas-covered trailers and 'erector launchers'—equipment used exclusively for Soviet SS-4 'Sandal' Medium-Range Ballistic Missiles (MRBMs). These are not defensive weapons. They are offensive nuclear delivery systems.\n\n**The Timeline:**\nThe construction is rapid. The CIA estimates that the sites will be fully operational in **10 to 13 days**. Once active, the missiles can be fueled and launched in under 20 minutes. This creates a 'Use it or Lose it' scenario for the President: if he waits too long to act, the missiles will be ready to fire, and any attempt to destroy them might trigger a launch."
