          "label": "Airstrike?",
          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/airstrike-doc.jpg",
          "credit": "JOINT CHIEFS MEMORANDUM - AI",
          "content": "### MEMORANDUM FOR THE PRESIDENT\n**FROM:** Joint Chiefs of Staff (JCS)\n**SUBJECT:** OPLAN 312 (Air Strike Plan)\n\n**The Military Position:**\nThe Joint Chiefs are unanimous. They view the placement of these missiles as a clandestine act of aggression that alters the status quo. General Curtis LeMay argues that the United States cannot tolerate a nuclear knife at its throat. He recommends **OPLAN 312**: a massive, surprise air attack to destroy the missile sites at sunrise, before they become operational.\n\n**The Moral Dilemma:**\nAttorney General Robert Kennedy (RFK) vehemently opposes a surprise attack. He passes a note to his brother: *\"I now know how Tojo felt when he was planning Pearl Harbor.\"* RFK argues that for the United States—a superpower and champion of democracy—to launch a surprise attack on a small island nation would be a moral catastrophe. It would destroy America's reputation and validate every piece of Soviet propaganda about 'American Imperialism.' The legal team struggles to find a justification for striking without a declaration of war."
        },
