          "label": "Threat Radius",
          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/cuba-missilerange.jpg",
          "credit": "CIA THREAT PROJECTION - AI",
          "content": "### THREAT RADIUS CALCULATION\n\n**Strategic Imbalance:**\nFor years, the Soviet Union has lived with US nuclear missiles in Turkey and Italy, right on their border. Now, Khrushchev is returning the favor. The SS-4 missiles in Cuba have a range of 1,000 miles. A second type, the SS-5 (also suspected), could travel 2,200 miles.\n\n**Target Analysis:**\n* **Washington D.C.:** 13 minutes flight time.\n* **New York City:** 15 minutes flight time.\n* **Strategic Air Command (Omaha):** Within range of SS-5s.\n\n**The MAD Factor:**\nThis destroys the current warning system. Usually, if the Soviets launched intercontinental missiles (ICBMs) from Russia, the US would have 25-30 minutes of radar warning—enough time to launch our own bombers (Mutually Assured Destruction). With missiles in Cuba, the warning time is cut to **5 minutes**. This effectively decapitates the US command structure before the President can reach a bunker. It is a destabilizing 'First Strike' capability."
