      "historicalOutcome": "### HISTORICAL OUTCOME: NEAR DISASTER\n\nThe US Navy **dropped the depth charges**. It was a terrifying mistake based on a lack of information. They did not know the submarine *B-59* was armed with a nuclear torpedo. The Soviet captain, thinking World War III had begun, ordered the torpedo to be armed. He was only stopped by the dissent of a fellow officer, Vasili Arkhipov. The world came within one unanimous vote of nuclear annihilation.",
