          "credit": "US NAVY FLAG PLOT - AI",
          "content": "### THE NAVY FLAG PLOT\n**TIME:** 10:00 AM EST, October 24\n\n**The Naval Cordon:**\nThe Quarantine has officially gone into effect. A massive arc of US Navy destroyers, cruisers, and aircraft carriers stretches across the Atlantic, 500 miles from the Cuban coast. The order is simple but terrifying: stop every ship bound for Cuba, search it, and turn back any carrying weapons.\n\n**The Confrontation:**\nTwo Soviet cargo ships, the *Gagarin* and the *Komiles*, are steaming toward the picket line. They are not slowing down. President Kennedy is managing the situation from the White House, demanding real-time updates. He is terrified that a local Navy commander might fire too early. He orders the line pulled back to give the Russian captains more time to receive orders from Moscow. The tension in the room is palpable; Secretary of State Dean Rusk whispers, *\"We're eyeball to eyeball, and I think the other fellow just blinked.\"*"
