          "credit": "TRACKING BOARD - AI",
          "content": "### RULES OF ENGAGEMENT (ROE)\n\n**The Submarine Threat:**\nSonar has detected Soviet submarines escorting the cargo ships. These subs are the 'wild cards.' They can slip past the blockade and attack US ships. The Navy has standing orders to force them to the surface.\n\n**The Signaling Procedure:**\nThe US Navy informs Moscow that they will drop 'practice depth charges'—low-yield explosives that make a loud bang but don't destroy the hull—to signal a submarine to surface and identify itself.\n\n**The Disconnect:**\nWhile this seems like a sound procedure in Washington, underwater it is chaos. The 'practice' charges sound exactly like real attacks to the terrified crew inside a steel tube. The Soviet commanders have not received clear instructions on how to handle this signaling. We are relying on the enemy understanding our rules, while we are attacking them."
