          "content": "### CONTACT REPORT: B-59\n\n**Target Acquired:**\nUS destroyers have cornered a Soviet Foxtrot-class submarine, the *B-59*, in the Sargasso Sea. They are dropping depth charges to force it up.\n\n**Conditions Onboard:**\nInside the B-59, conditions are hellish. The air conditioning has failed, temperatures are over 100°F, and carbon dioxide levels are dangerously high. The crew is fainting from heat exhaustion. They have been cut off from radio contact with Moscow for days.\n\n**The Critical Intelligence Gap:**\nWhat the US Navy does *not* know is that the B-59 is carrying a **Special Weapon**: a nuclear-tipped torpedo with the explosive power of the Hiroshima bomb. The Captain, Valentin Savitsky, believes the war has already started. He has the physical capability to launch the nuke without codes from Moscow. By dropping charges on him, we are practically begging him to fire back."
