          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/u2photos.jpg",
          "credit": "SA-2 Site - US Department of Defense",
          "content": "### LOSING CONTROL\n\n**Field Analysis:**\nThe shootdown changes the calculus of the entire crisis. Until now, the assumption was that Khrushchev was in tight control of his forces. Intelligence analysts are now scrambling to answer a terrifying question: *Did Khrushchev order this?*\n\n**The Rogue Theory:**\nThe CIA suspects that the order to fire came from a local Soviet commander in Cuba, acting out of panic or zeal, without authorization from Moscow. This is the 'Fog of War' in action. If the US retaliates against a mistake, it forces the Soviet Union to defend its troops, triggering a spiral of escalation that neither leader can stop. The legal justification for self-defense is clear, but the strategic consequence is Armageddon."
