          "credit": "Jupiter Missiles - Lewis Mills",
          "content": "### KHRUSHCHEV'S LETTERS\n\n**The Mixed Signals:**\nIn the chaos of the final days, the White House receives two conflicting messages from Moscow.\n1.  **Friday Night Letter:** A long, rambling, emotional teletype message from Khrushchev. He speaks of the horror of war and offers to remove the missiles if the US simply promises not to invade Cuba.\n2.  **Saturday Morning Letter:** A stiff, formal, public broadcast. It raises the price. It demands the US remove its Jupiter missiles from Turkey in exchange for the Soviet withdrawal from Cuba.\n\n**The Dilemma:**\nThe 'Turkey Trade' is logically fair—trading missiles for missiles. But politically, it is impossible. If the US publicly removes missiles from a NATO ally (Turkey) under Soviet threat, NATO will collapse. The Generals demand the President reject the trade."
