          "content": "### THE 'CORDIER PLOY'\n\n**The Diplomatic Trick:**\nKennedy and his advisors devise a brilliant strategy to solve the 'Two Letter' problem. They decide to **ignore** the second, harsh letter and respond only to the first, reasonable one. They will accept the 'Non-Invasion Pledge' publicly.\n\n**The Shadow Negotiation:**\nSimultaneously, the President sends his brother, RFK, to the Soviet Embassy to meet Ambassador Dobrynin. The message is a secret ultimatum: *\"We cannot make a public deal about Turkey. It would destroy NATO. BUT... if you take your missiles out of Cuba, ours will be gone from Turkey in four to five months. We just can't write it down.\"* It is a handshake deal based on trust between enemies."
