          "content": "### RESOLUTION\n**DATE:** October 28, 1962\n\n**The Broadcast:**\nThe tension breaks at 9:00 AM the next morning. Radio Moscow broadcasts a message from Khrushchev: *\"The Soviet government has issued a new order on the dismantling of the weapons which you describe as 'offensive' and their return to the Soviet Union.\"*\n\n**The Aftermath:**\nKennedy orders the Quarantine lifted. The Soviet ships turn back. The world breathes a collective sigh of relief. \n\n**Legacy:**\nThe 'Turkey Trade' remains a state secret for decades. Kennedy is hailed as a hero who stared down the Soviets without blinking. Khrushchev is viewed as weak by his own Politburo and is ousted from power two years later. But history now recognizes that it was compromise, empathy, and secret diplomacy—not just brute force—that saved the world from incineration."
